# Prettier ignore — intent-eval-lab
#
# Machine-generated eval-result files under research/*/results/** are not
# authored prose; formatting them produces noise and renders the advisory
# prettier-md gate permanently red. Exclude every baseline's results dir so
# the gate carries real signal on authored docs only.
#
# NOTE: the doc-quality.yml prettier step passes BOTH --ignore-path .gitignore
# AND --ignore-path .prettierignore (prettier 3.x honors multiple ignore
# paths). A bare .prettierignore is NOT auto-read when --ignore-path is set
# explicitly, so the workflow flag is load-bearing.
research/**/results/**

# Vendored upstream snapshots + the vendored audit-harness are commit-pinned
# verbatim copies (the latter is hash-pinned in .harness-hash). They must stay
# byte-identical, so they are not ours to reformat.
_vendor/**
specs/_vendor/**
.audit-harness/**

# Constituent-project symlinks (gitignored; not part of this repo's CI checkout).
projects/**

# Frozen brief-pack — verbatim point-in-time copies captured for the 2026-05-26
# plan audit; reformatting them would falsify the snapshot.
000-docs/audit/2026-05-26-plan-audit/brief-pack/**

# Offline self-test corpus parsed literally by scripts/classifier-walls.py — its
# byte shape is load-bearing for the substring pre-wall; keep it byte-stable.
specs/drift-classification/v1/examples/**

# DERIVED dashboard — regenerated by scripts/detector-health.py and gated by its
# own `--check` freshness comparison (CI "Validate specs and docs"). Its bytes are
# owned by the generator, not prettier; reformatting it breaks the freshness gate.
docs/detector-health.md

# DERIVED dashboard — regenerated by scripts/render-sak-dashboard.py and gated by
# its own `--check` freshness comparison (CI "Validate specs and docs"). Same
# rationale as detector-health.md: the generator owns the bytes, so prettier must
# not touch it or the freshness gate would fight the formatter.
SAK-DASHBOARD.md
